# Apoint Design System

Appointment booking SaaS. Feel: Uber, Airbnb, Apple, Linear, Notion — human-designed, minimal, production-ready. Never generic AI SaaS aesthetics.

## Avoid

Emojis in UI, neon/glow, glassmorphism, heavy gradients, excessive shadows, fancy animations, generic dashboard templates, 3-column feature cards, bright blue accents, visual clutter, too many borders/icons/badges.

## Colors

- Primary: `#000000` (black), `#FFFFFF` (white)
- Green: success only
- Red: errors, cancellation, destructive actions
- Mostly monochrome — no other accent colors unless requested

## Layout & Typography

- Large breathing space, generous padding/margins, calm uncluttered pages
- Typography is the hero: large headings, clear hierarchy, minimal copy
- Mobile-first, strong visual hierarchy, clean alignment

## Components (Tailwind)

**Buttons:** large, rounded, black bg + white text
```jsx
<button className="rounded-full bg-black px-6 py-3 text-white">Book</button>
```

**Cards:** minimal, soft radius, little/no shadow
```jsx
<div className="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 p-6">...</div>
```

**Inputs:** large, touch-friendly, clean borders
```jsx
<input className="w-full rounded-lg border border-neutral-300 px-4 py-3" />
```

## Stack & Structure

React + Tailwind CSS. Mobile responsive. Reusable components, clean folder organization. Usability first — real product screens, not design showcases. No placeholder-heavy UIs.

## Product Context

Users: browse professionals, view profiles, check availability, book/manage appointments.
Professionals: manage availability, view bookings, update status.
Tone: trustworthy, premium, simple.
